HEADWORD: Triphthongal
<hw>Triph*thon"gal</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <def>Of or
pertaining to a triphthong; consisting of three vowel sounds pronounced
together in a single syllable.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

